ORE-CARRYING CORPORATION, Libelant, v. CORNELL STEAMSHIP COMPANY, Respondent-Appellee, and United States, Respondent-Appellant, and three other cases. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 2, 1927. No. 309. Duncan & Mount, of New York City (O. D. Duncan and Dudley C. Smith, both of New York City, of counsel), for the United States. Kirlin, Woolsey, Campbell, Hickox & Keating, of New York City (Robert S. Er-skine and Henry P. Elliott, both of New York City, of counsel), for Cornell Steamboat Co.

Before MANTON and SWAN, Circuit Judges, and CAMPBELL, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Decrees affirmed, with costs.
